column1: Feature 1 (number of 1st person pronouns) 75 (liwc_i) 133 (receptiviti_emotionally_aware) 164 (receptiviti_self_conscious) are both chosen at both 1k and 32k input data. Choosing number of 1st person pronouns and liwc_i may because using more 1st person pronouns like 'I' means that the commentor is more likely to be egocentric. Self-consciousness means that the commentor might be more self-centered. Emotional awareness means that the commentor is likely to be more sensitive to people's emotion. These features corelate with the political persuasion of the commentor.

P-values are generally lower given more data. More input data means that the selector can be more confident in the significance of the chosen features. Lower p-value means that the chosen features better separate the classes.

Feature 1 (number of 1st person pronouns) 75 (liwc_i) 133 (receptiviti_emotionally_aware) 150 (receptiviti_intellectural) 164 (receptiviti_self_conscious) are the top 5 features. People belong to certain class are more likely to be self-centered (using more 1st person pronouns and self-consciousness). Certain class of people could be more sensitive to emotions. These features can help to differentiate their political persuasion.
